---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Rockstar Files New Trademarks for GTA VI Online">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-8 pb-16">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <div class="text-sm text-muted mb-6">
      <a href="/news" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">News</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-muted/60">Rockstar Files New Trademarks</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Category & Date -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-neon-pink/10 text-neon-pink border border-neon-pink/20">Official News</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-muted">June 27, 2026</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-6">
      Rockstar Files New Trademarks for <span class="gradient-text">GTA VI Online</span>
    </h1>

    <!-- Featured Image -->
    <div class="aspect-video rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1626814026160-2237a95fc5a0?w=1200&q=80" alt="GTA VI Online trademarks" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
    </div>

    <!-- Share Buttons -->
    <div class="flex gap-3 mb-8">
      <button class="glass px-4 py-2 rounded-xl text-sm text-muted hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-x-twitter mr-2"></i>Share
      </button>
      <button class="glass px-4 py-2 rounded-xl text-sm text-muted hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-reddit mr-2"></i>Share
      </button>
      <button class="glass px-4 py-2 rounded-xl text-sm text-muted hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-link mr-2"></i>Copy Link
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none text-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p class="text-white text-xl font-light leading-relaxed">
        Rockstar Games has filed a series of new trademarks that strongly suggest the company is laying the groundwork for Grand Theft Auto VI's online multiplayer component, tentatively titled <strong>"GTA VI Online."</strong>
      </p>

      <p>
        The filings, discovered by eagle-eyed trademark watchers at the US Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO), include trademarks for "GTA VI Online," "Leonida Online," and several other branding marks that point toward a fully-fledged multiplayer experience launching alongside or shortly after the single-player campaign.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-white font-display text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What the Trademarks Reveal</h2>

      <p>
        The trademarks cover a wide range of categories including downloadable software, online gaming services, virtual currency, and merchandise. Notably, "Leonida Online" suggests that Rockstar may be branding the multiplayer component after the game's fictional state of Leonida, similar to how "Los Santos" became synonymous with GTA Online.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-neon-pink pl-6 my-8 italic text-white/80">
        "This is a clear signal that Rockstar is taking the lessons learned from GTA Online and building a more robust, more scalable platform from day one."
        <footer class="text-sm text-muted mt-2">— Industry Analyst</footer>
      </blockquote>

      <h2 class="text-white font-display text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What This Means for Players</h2>

      <p>
        Based on the scope of the filings, here's what players can potentially expect from GTA VI's online mode:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
        <li>A persistent open world set across the entire Leonida map, not just a single city.</li>
        <li>Enhanced player housing and businesses with more customization options.</li>
        <li>Dynamic weather and environmental events that affect gameplay in real-time.</li>
        <li>Improved anti-cheat measures and player reporting systems.</li>
        <li>Cross-platform play between PlayStation 5 and Xbox Series X|S.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-white font-display text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Community Reaction</h2>

      <p>
        The GTA community has responded with cautious optimism. While GTA Online was a massive financial success for Rockstar, many players felt the single-player content was neglected in favor of multiplayer updates. Rockstar has already confirmed that GTA VI will receive story DLC, suggesting a more balanced approach this time around.
      </p>

      <p>
        As always, we'll keep you updated as more details emerge. Stay tuned to hubgta6.com for the latest news and analysis.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Articles -->
    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/5">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl mb-6">Related Articles</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="#" class="group flex gap-4 bg-card rounded-xl p-4 border border-white/5 hover:border-white/10 transition-all">
          <div class="w-24 h-16 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shrink-0">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1553481180-ed2468b0c677?w=200&q=80" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium group-hover:text-neon-cyan transition-colors line-clamp-2">Leaked Gameplay Shows Expanded Leonida Map</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">June 25, 2026</p>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="#" class="group flex gap-4 bg-card rounded-xl p-4 border border-white/5 hover:border-white/10 transition-all">
          <div class="w-24 h-16 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shrink-0">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504608524841-42fe6f032b4b?w=200&q=80" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium group-hover:text-neon-cyan transition-colors line-clamp-2">GTA VI Will Feature Dynamic Weather Systems</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">June 22, 2026</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
